citeturn15view1turn34search0turn31view0  

The securitisation evidence base is strongest for repeat issuers where rating agencies publish structural and surveillance summaries. Together 2024‑2ND1 provides a clear window into how second‑lien risk is packaged: multiple tranches, meaningful senior CE (25%), explicit liquidity protection via a funded reserve, and hedging of fixed‑rate exposures into SONIA liabilities. citeturn15view1  

Performance history is harder to evidence without investor report access, but DBRS surveillance actions provide a public baseline for at least one seasoned deal (Together 2022‑2ND1), including rated‑note outcomes (confirmed ratings) and disclosed modelling parameters. citeturn15view2